name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: When the S&P 500 doesn't close beneath the December low during Q1 the returns the full year are extremely strong.  Up 18.4% on average and higher 33 out of 35 times.  It just happened again in '21, which could have bulls smiling.  https://t.co/bfy0rXP5uv

name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: The S&P 500 gained 53.7% the previous 4 quarters, the most ever.  What happened after the other best 4 quarter returns?  Returns 2 quarters later are muted. Yet, going out a full 4 quarters, the overall bull trend returned.  In other words, a break after huge gains is normal.  https://t.co/Oq05P1765u

name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: S&P 500 up >5% four quarters in a row and what happened a year later?  Q3 '54     +35.2% Q4 '58     +8.5% Q2 '83     -8.9% Q4 '95     +20.2% Q1 '21      ???

name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: The S&P 500 is up >5% 4 consecutive quarters.  It made it to 5 only once, in Q4 '54.  Up another 26% a year later back then.

name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: S&P 500 up the past 4 quarters and up more than 50% over this time (+53.7%).  The only other time in history that ever happened? Off of the '82 lows.  S&P 500 was up 4 quarters in a row and up 53.4% at the end of Q2 in '83.  Be aware, the next year though the S&P 500 was down 9%.

name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: Over the past 22 quarters the S&P 500 has been higher 19 of them.

name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: The December Indicator signaled in '21.  This is when the S&P 500 December closing low isn't violated in Q1. It tends to be quite bullish for the full year.  Full year avg return (since '50) is 18.4% and higher 33 of 35 years.

name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: Another similarity between now and '10.  Besides both the March '09 and March '20 lows kicking off the best starts to a new bull market ever, turns out '10 saw a lower January and then higher Feb and March for the S&P 500.  Remember that '10 was quite rocky in the summer.

name: Ryan Detrick, CMT
tweet: We noted April has been extremely strong for stocks lately, up 14 of the past 15 years.  After just 6 trading days in '21, the S&P 500 is up another 4%.  https://t.co/sNhLKKZw1M
